line_2: And quail'd by labour, gain'd the shore at last,

line_1: Forth to that forked hill they silent pac'd;
line_2: Where hid in studious shades their fruitless hours they waste.

line_1: Through many a devious path at length he paced,
line_2: 'Till to a mountain hoare they come at last;

line_1: Through many a devious path at length he paced,
line_2: Whose high-rais'd brows with silvan honours graced,

line_1: Through many a devious path at length he paced,
line_2: And over all an aweful horrour cast.
